## Project identity: KAIRO

**KAIRO** is a local-first, voice-driven **developer assistant** and **persistent runtime companion**—not a chat-and-forget chatbot. It observes workflow context over time and builds **structured memory** so it can assist by voice, run tools when appropriate, and improve as patterns emerge.

Roadmap is phased: (1) wake word, STT, local LLM, TTS, basic tools; (2) screen/window/browser/clipboard awareness and semantic activity + memory engine; (3) long-term learning, workflow prediction, connectors, Redis Streams bus, dialogue planning. Target stack includes Porcupine/openWakeWord, faster-whisper, Qwen-class local LLM, Piper TTS, SQLite memory, Redis Streams. Details: `kairo/README.md`.

---

This codebase implements that vision as a **modular macOS assistant runtime** (Windows adapter planned).

Rules:

Never generate a monolithic script.

Always separate:

core runtime
tool registry
platform adapters
memory layer
gesture services
voice services
state machine

Platform-specific logic must live only inside adapters/mac.

Intent routing must NOT execute tools directly.

Use dependency injection between modules.

Tools must register dynamically using registry pattern.

State machine must be explicit and isolated.

Assistant runtime must support future Windows adapter later.

All configs must live in config/*.yaml

Session lifecycle must be implemented as state transitions, not booleans.